beer.beer_description: Drink it in. Big, dark and spicy throughout. Banana and dark chocolate tones that add texture and grip. An addition of salt water from the Cape Jaffa jetty in the kettle adds a moreish dimension to harmonise with the sweeter caramel malts. Good to go or bury in your cellar for another hard time ahead.

items.badge_description: A global celebration of beer, International Beer Day toasts beers worldwide. Like a helles from Germany, a tripel from Belgian, an ESB from Britain, a pilsner from the Czech Republic, or a hazy IPA from USA. Thanks for celebrating global beers!
Beer is often better with friends. Besides, drinking socially is what we're all about! You've checked in with at least 10 other people within 5 hours.
Drinking with friends is fun. Right? You've checked in with at least 4 other people within 2 hours.
So, you're new around here? Congrats on your first brew! This one's for you.

Thanks for staying at home, and checking in with Untappd! It allows us to stay connected to a community of beer lovers, just like you, even if we can't be in the same physical location. From our home to yours, cheers and stay safe!
Happy Untappd anniversary to you! Thanks for sticking around and drinking socially with us. Cheers! That's 7 years on Untappd!

items.checkin_comment: Loopholes are to lousy lawyers what G-spots are to lousy lovers. This a great find, however, from this brewer down Robe way.  Roasty, spicy, malty, caramel and yeast; and most of all it contains love, as it says on the can.  A real rib tickler, this.
